During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced that President Biden has extended the pause on federal student loan repayments through August 31st. The extension is aimed at providing financial relief to borrowers and improving student loan programs. Psaki also discussed the need for COVID-19 funding and criticized Senate Republicans for obstructing the process. She highlighted the importance of providing resources to combat the pandemic and protect American lives. Additionally, Psaki announced the authorization of an additional $100 million in security assistance to Ukraine to help them defend against Russian aggression. The assistance includes Javelin anti-armor systems, which have proven effective in combating Russian tanks. Psaki also mentioned that the administration is working with allies to provide Ukraine with additional capabilities.